\end{aligned}
$$

5. Sometimes grouping symbols occur within other grouping symbols. When you encounter this, work within the innermost set of grouping symbols first and work your way outward.

Simplify

$3\left[8 x(2 x-1)-4\left(3 x^{2}-2 x+5\right)\right]-\left(3 x^{2}+7 x-5\right)$

There are two sets of ( ) inside the [ ]. Begin work with them.

$3\left[8 x(2 x-1)-4\left(3 x^{2}-2 x+5\right)\right]-\left(3 x^{2}+7 x-5\right)$

$=3\left[16 x^{2}-8 x-12 x^{2}+8 x-20\right]-3 x^{2}-7 x+5$

$=3\left[4 x^{2}+0 x-20\right]-3 x^{2}-7 x+5$

$=12 x^{2}-60-3 x^{2}-7 x+5$

$=9 x^{2}-7 x-55$

